problem: How many numbers are in the list $ -36, -29, -22, \ldots, 41, 48?$
solution: Add 1 to each member of the list to get $-35,-28,-21,\ldots,42,49$, and divide by 7 to get $-5$,$-4$,$-3$,$\ldots$, $6$,$7$.  Adding 6 to each number in the list gives the list $1,2,3,\ldots,12,13$, so there are $\boxed{13}$ numbers.

## Step 1: Identify the pattern of the sequence
The sequence increases by 7 each time.

## Step 2: Determine the starting and ending points of the sequence
The sequence starts at -36 and ends at 48.

## Step 3: Find the difference between the starting and ending points
The difference between the starting and ending points is 48 - (-36) = 84.

## Step 4: Divide the difference by the common difference and add 1 to find the number of terms
The common difference is 7, so dividing the difference by the common difference gives 84 / 7 = 12. Adding 1 to this result gives 12 + 1 = 13.
